metadata.name: Treasured Rug #111
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

metadata.name: Hex Gorilla Munchies #24
metadata.description: The Hex Gorilla Universe, a multi-chain, collaborative art and NFT collection, focuses on the use and appreciation of a diverse spectrum of colors that enrich our lives. When utilized successfully, color has a way of influencing our emotions and forming relationships, whether it's your favorite combination of paints and other mediums or the website you visit every day.

metadata.name: The Climb #142
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, it’s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

“The Climb” is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.


Everything is written in javascript and p5js.
It can sometimes take a little while to render on older computers.

metadata.name: Alleles #200
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Detailed investigation of the presented genetic information suggests subject may posess a predeliction for intermittent episodes of delusions of grandeur and lack of self-confidence, yet also posesses an aptitude for unparalled creative problem solving abilities and determination. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 200-207cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 78-82 years.

metadata.name: aprendizajes #360
metadata.description:
aprendizajes is a generative art project that pays a tribute to the process of learning. 25% of primary proceeds go to Save The Children. Full description of the artwork+instructions here: https://www.iillucid.com/aprendizajes/

The artwork allows the user to:

* Change resolution: press 'd' followed by any number from 1 to 9 to add that amount to the pixel density. If you get a black screen you have surpassed what your graphics card can handle: press d + 0 to reset the pixel density. You can fine tune pressing d followed by + or - (+/- 0.5).
* Save image: press 's' to save the current image as png. For a higher resolution png, 1st increase the resolution using 'd' and then save the image with 's'.
* Tune image parameters: press 'z' (brightness), 'x' (contrast), 'g' (gamma), 'b' (blur) followed by + or - to adjust. Toggle tuning with 'a'. Press 'n' then + or - to adjust amount of noise.
* Redraw: 'r' (changes how lines are drawn)

It is recommended to read the full instructions on the article.

metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

metadata.name: Avoidance #293
metadata.description: Created with Javascript and p5js. Each bar steers clear of the other bars and balls. This is an experiment in which I admittedly invested a little too much time. The numerous variables, factors, and variants ensure that each mint has a distinct outcome.

metadata.name: Unfolded #291
metadata.description:
A plane is repeatedly folded over itself, choosing creases either at random, or according to some pattern (like a grid). These creases form the boundaries of the individual textured tiles.

Once the folds are complete, they are undone in reverse order, recreating the original plane. With each unfolding, the orientation of each crease (as a mountain or a valley), and each tile (facing up or down) is recorded as a sequence of 1s and 0s. Tiles are colored and textured according to similarities in these binary sequences, giving rise to subtle symmetries and repetitions.

Written in vanilla JS & HTML5 Canvas.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #444
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #71
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side

metadata.name: ASSEMBLING MACHINE #39
metadata.description:
The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.
---------------
Collectors at the highest tier (125 tez) may claim a signed 8”x10” print of their mint. Please look for details about prints on Twitter (@teaboswell), or contact me directly
---------------
CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines
B - Cycle border sizes (0 -> 100 -> 200 -> 300px)

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------

metadata.name: Sketch D #7
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch D (Disruption). The grid is broken. The color palette from Sketches A, B, and C remains. Most outputs are simply single colors or black and white. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

Press the spacebar to see the unDisturbed structure.

metadata.name: Block Dock #37
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

Is it a space dock? Is it a ship dock? Where are they docking... and why?

'Block Dock' is a playful exploration of scale, form and color.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #1558
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.
